# ISO 9001:2015 – Quality Management System (QMS) Checklist

**Purpose:**  
ISO 9001 defines the framework for a Quality Management System (QMS) focused on meeting customer requirements and enhancing satisfaction.  
It applies to any organization seeking consistent product/service quality, process efficiency, and continuous improvement.

---

| Clause | Requirement | Description | Status (✓/✗) | Remarks |
|---------|--------------|-------------|---------------|---------|
| 4.1 | Context of the Organization | Identify internal and external issues affecting quality objectives. |  |  |
| 4.2 | Interested Parties | Determine relevant stakeholders and their expectations. |  |  |
| 4.3 | Scope | Define the scope of the QMS. |  |  |
| 4.4 | QMS and Processes | Establish, implement, and maintain processes with performance criteria. |  |  |
| 5.1 | Leadership & Commitment | Ensure top management demonstrates leadership and commitment to QMS. |  |  |
| 5.2 | Quality Policy | Develop and communicate a quality policy aligned with company objectives. |  |  |
| 5.3 | Organizational Roles | Define responsibilities and authorities within the QMS. |  |  |
| 6.1 | Risks and Opportunities | Identify and address quality-related risks and opportunities. |  |  |
| 6.2 | Quality Objectives | Establish measurable quality objectives at relevant functions. |  |  |
| 7.1 | Resources | Determine and provide necessary resources. |  |  |
| 7.2 | Competence | Ensure personnel are competent based on education, training, or experience. |  |  |
| 7.3 | Awareness | Ensure staff are aware of QMS policy, objectives, and their contribution. |  |  |
| 7.5 | Documented Information | Control QMS documentation, records, and changes. |  |  |
| 8.1 | Operational Planning | Plan, implement, and control product/service realization. |  |  |
| 8.2 | Customer Requirements | Determine and review requirements for products/services. |  |  |
| 8.3 | Design & Development | Establish design/development controls. |  |  |
| 8.4 | Control of External Providers | Evaluate and monitor suppliers. |  |  |
| 8.5 | Production & Service Provision | Implement controlled conditions for production. |  |  |
| 8.7 | Control of Nonconformity | Handle nonconforming outputs appropriately. |  |  |
| 9.1 | Monitoring & Measurement | Analyze performance and customer satisfaction. |  |  |
| 9.2 | Internal Audit | Conduct internal audits to verify QMS conformity. |  |  |
| 9.3 | Management Review | Review QMS effectiveness at planned intervals. |  |  |
| 10.2 | Nonconformity & Corrective Action | Address nonconformities and take corrective actions. |  |  |
| 10.3 | Continual Improvement | Implement actions for continuous QMS improvement. |  |  |
